sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2044014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Based on our project, <1,4> is the direct pathway from Site No.1 to Site No.4 in the map we design.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: According to our DNA sequence design from Site NO.1 to Site NO.4, we give the post-20 complementary base pairs from Site NO.1 and Pre-20 complementary base pairs from Site NO.4 plus 12bp information bit in the middle to HongXun Biological Science and Technology Co., Ltd in SuZhou, Jiangsu province, who will help us synthesize a DNA single strand from Site NO.1 to Site NO.4.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It is a segment of DNA comprised by post-20 complementary base pairs from Site NO.1 and pre-20 complementary base pairs from Site NO.4 plus 12bp information bit in the middle, which is used to connect Site NO.1 with Site NO.4.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Every site contains 40bp DNA sequence at random nd every adjacent site is connected by ???line???, which adds up to 13 lines. Lines are represented by 52bp DNA single strand, with post-20 complementary base pairs from the first and pre-20 complementary base pairs from the last site plus 12bp information bit in the middle. The pre-4bp sequences contain the information of identification point, the mid-4bp sequences contain the information of the specified line, and the post-4bp contain the information of the path length in the map.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ding Haojie
